{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"838a72a9-acbb-46b1-a137-ebfccd28829c","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's general guidance for the switch:\n\n### 1. NuGet.org Setup\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Configure trusted publishers**\n- Add a new **GitHub Actions** trusted publisher, specifying your repo owner, name, and the workflow filename\n\n### 2. Workflow Changes\n\n**Add OIDC permissions** to your job:\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token request\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step:**\n\nBefore:\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n    --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n    --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nAfter:\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n    --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nThat's it — no API key needed. The `dotnet` CLI automatically detects the OIDC token from the GitHub Actions environment when trusted publishing is configured.\n\n### 3. Cleanup\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository **Settings → Secrets**\n- Revoke the old API key on nuget.org\n\n### Key Points\n- The OIDC token is **short-lived** and scoped to the workflow run — more secure than a long-lived API key\n- Requires `dotnet` SDK **8.0.400+** or the [`nuget/setup-nuget`](https://github.com/nuget/setup-nuget) action\n- If your workflow sets `permissions` at the **workflow level**, make sure `id-token: write` is included there too\n\nWould you like me to create a sample workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7387bec2-7400-4e84-acd0-ed7d1b589ce3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to OIDC trusted publishing. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":486,"requestId":"C013:3E203F:12B9DA:166E8F:69EABEF1"},"id":"964760b7-f6b1-4143-ac23-b19bcb2b9487","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:53:16.705Z","parentId":"5930dbc4-02bf-4e52-8f1a-cdab89bad574"}
